<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="87" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Individuals of this species were in flower when collected in August and November, with fruits likely becoming mature ca. 5-6 months later.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="87" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">I am pleased to name this new species after my husband, Gregory Hora, to whom I am most grateful for his assistance in collecting this and other species across Fiji.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" type="phylogenetic placement">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Phylogenetic placement.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">
A recent phylogenetic study by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.07.004" author="Johnson, MA" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="16" pageNumber="101" pagination="30 - 48" refId="B10" refString="Johnson, MA, Clark, JR, Wagner, WL, McDade, LA, 2017. A molecular phylogeny of the Pacific clade of Cyrtandra reveals a Fijian origin, recent diversification, and the importance of founder events. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 116: 30 - 48, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.07.004" title="A molecular phylogeny of the Pacific clade of Cyrtandra reveals a Fijian origin, recent diversification, and the importance of founder events." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.07.004" volume="116" year="2017">Johnson et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. A. Johnson" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyrtandra gregoryi" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gregoryi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Cyrtandra gregoryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sister to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. ciliata" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">C. ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with strong support (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. A portion of the Maximum Likelihood phylogram from Johnson et al. (2017) based on three nuclear (ITS, ETS, Cyrt 1) and two chloroplast (psb A- trn H, rpl 32 - trn L) loci. Support values shown for each branch are bootstrap and posterior probabilities when ≥ 50 % and ≥ 0.50, respectively. An asterisk indicates 100 % BS or 1.0 PP; a dash indicates that the branch was not supported." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.91.21623.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174657" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">4</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyrtandra ciliata" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="87">Cyrtandra ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Fijian islands of Vanua Levu, Taveuni, and Koro from 300-1100 m 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="88" start="start">elevation</pageBreakToken>
. These species share a cymose inflorescence and glabrous to glabrate leaves. The key provided in the taxonomic treatment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gillett, GW" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" pagination="107 - 159" refId="B5" refString="Gillett, GW, 1967. The genus Cyrtandra in Fiji. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 37: 107 - 159" title="The genus Cyrtandra in Fiji." volume="37" year="1967">Gillett (1967)</bibRefCitation>
would place 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. gregoryi" pageId="3" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="gregoryi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="88">C. gregoryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in species Group 5 based on the branching cyme inflorescence, non-woody inflorescence axis, deciduous calyx, styles and/or stamens being exserted from the corolla tube, and stamens 8-12 mm long.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="1138465" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.91.21623.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174657" pageId="3" pageNumber="88" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="88">Figure 4.</emphasis>
A portion of the Maximum Likelihood phylogram from 
